**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************
 
                  An alternative to tetramer based fingerprinting.

**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************

The basic idea is that you call ORFs using prodigal, GeneMark etc. Then you calculate a codon usage 
profile for the entire contig based only on the sequences of the ORFs within that contig. This
software is a collection of XX scripts which work in the following way

	cub.pl                 -- Main wrapper
        callOrfs.pl            -- Wrapper for gene calling software (default: prodigal)
	squishOrfs.pl          -- Put all the orfs from a single contig into one big lump
        barcodeByCU.pl         -- Create a barcode based on a squished fasta file

I wouldn't predict that this approach would work well on a set of Genes as each gene is likely 
to display a CU profile based more on functionality, rather than origin. However YMMV... I have
written this software as part of a broader bininng pipeline which takes long (>5KB) microbial
contigs as input.

